description.narrative: In 2021, UNICEF Egypt mobilised and leveraged resources for children through private sector companies’ contributions and deepened its engagement with National Committee through regular updates and targeted communication.Fundraising efforts with the private sector yielded US$ 1.2 million in flexible funding for programmes, and a firm funding pipeline of US$ 370,000 for early 2022.UNICEF, in 2021 leveraged non-financial business for results partnerships with an estimated value of $2.3 million against a target of $1.3 million. The various initiatives supported COVID-19 vaccination uptake, hygiene promotion, nutrition as well as training 100 vulnerable young people by the private sector.; | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:13/12/2021
